    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Information</head>
      <p>Astoria Beneficial Club (ABC) began as a social club in
         1901, but eventually became a beneficial club that paid out
         sick dues and burial benefits to its members. Astoria donated
         money to organizations that benefitted the community, such as
         the NAACP and the local Colored YMCA, and to individuals in
         need. The Club also set up scholarships at Virginia Union
         University and honored individuals and businesses in the area
         for their community service. The Astoria Beneficial Club is
         still active in Richmond.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>The collection includes minutes, correspondence, committee
         reports and other materials. The date range of these archives
         spans the years 1906 to 1947. The minutes are from the years
         1906 to 1909, 1911 to 1927, 1935 to 1941, 1943, and 1947.
         There are minutes missing from each of the above years.</p>
    </scopecontent>
